sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by LuxR in concert with HSL

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the LuxR activator protein complexed with the autoinducer, 3-oxo-hexanoyl-HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules of the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: c2 P22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: c2 repressor from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The P22 c2 repressor protein coding sequence is a 720 base-pair sequence with the standard RBS-compatible BioBrick prefix and the standard BioBrick suffix sections on its ends. It binds to the P22 c2 regulatory sequence, BBa_R0053. The sequence contains a LVA tag for faster degredation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746365
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PLL promoter taken from the P4 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PLL promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746351
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: plasmid DNA supplied by Prof. Richard Calendar, University of California.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The pag activator taken from PSP3 phage acts on a class of inducible promoters (parts I746360 to I746365), inducing their activity to varying degrees. The part sequence does already contain a ribosome binding site (B0034)!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part does contain a RBS (B0034) already.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
